narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Overall great class to learn about Indonesian music, culture, and society. It's fun, relaxed, and you learn so much! Highly recommend.
If you're interested in learning a new form of music in a relaxed and laid-back setting, then take it!
Maho is leaving for a year but the course will be taught by legendary Pak Sumarsam, an equally warm and humbling man. Take this course to broaden your Yale experience.
Really cool class but not a gut. Definetely recommend for a second semester senior.
Take it! It's not really that a huge gut like you would imagine, because there are weekly assignments. But it's an interesting, fun, and easy course.
Ends up being more work than you think because there are responses for every class but in the big scheme still not too much and class time is very enjoyable.
As a School of Music student I would definitely recommend this performance class.
